                    <div>
                        <p class="topic-list">${DADOS_ADICIONAIS}</p>

                        <p class="topic-item">1) Conference:</p>
                        <p class="topic-list">1.1 - When you receive the purchase order, check if your invoice will be a mirror of the purchase order.</p>
                        <p class="topic-list">1.2 - If the purchase order is not in accordance with the invoice billing, contact the buyer who sent your order, before issuing the invoice.</p>
                        <p class="topic-list">1.3 - Remembering that you will be asked to cancel the Invoice, if any Divergence with the purchase order. Return shipping will be the responsibility of the supplier.</p>

                        <p class="topic-item">2) Invoice Issuance:</p>
                        <p class="topic-list">2.1 - It is essential that the purchase order number is informed in the note field of your invoice.</p>
                        <p class="topic-list">2.2 - Check if the Invoice to be invoiced is correct and in accordance with the purchase order received, consider checking: Quantities, Taxes and ISS service code (in case of service provision).</p>
                        <p class="topic-list"><b>2.3 - The issuance of the invoice must be generated by the 20th of the current month. If issued after the date informed, it will be returned for cancellation and re-billing in the following month.</b></p>
                        <p class="topic-list">2.4 - Once the invoice is generated, XML file must be sent (in case of Material) and PDF file to email nfe@caoamontadora.com.br</a></p>
                        <p class="topic-list">2.5 - Also send the PDF file of the invoice to the email provided in the Delivery Data.</p>

                        <p class="topic-item">3) Realization of the Service:</p>
                        <p class="topic-list">3.1 - Alignment of date and time with the business/technical area responsible for the service request. Contacts through of Delivery Data on the order form.</p>

                        <p class="topic-item">4) Material delivery:</p>
                        <p class="topic-list">4.1 - Receipt only takes place from Monday to Friday.</p>
                        <p class="topic-list">4.2 - Reception hours from 08:00 to 13:00 hours.</p>
                        <p class="topic-list">4.3 - Confirm with the requesting area, through the Delivery Data in the order form, the day and time that the delivery will be carried out so as not to cause inconvenience.</p>

                        <p class="topic-item">5) Payment:</p>
                        <p class="topic-list">5.1 - Payment will be provided by the requesting area, after the service or delivery of the material and receipt of the PDF of the invoice by email, as stated in the previous items.</p>
                        <p class="topic-list">5.2 - Payments will be made via bank deposit in legal current account (in the same CNPJ and Corporate Name as the order issued), according to the negotiated payment method.</p>
                        <!-- EMAIL OUTLOOK - ELEMENTO HTML DEVE RECEBER APENAS UMA CLASSE DE ESTILO -->
                        <p class="topic-list"><span class="highlight-lightgreen">
                            5.3 - Payments are being made exclusively on Mondays, Wednesdays and Fridays. For maturities that coincide with Tuesdays and Thursdays, payments will be made on the following day.
                        </span></p>
                        
